1:99.name: Configuration=standard, State=enabled
1:99.description:
Standard Icon buttons are low-emphasis buttons.
They are used for the lowest priority actions, especially when presenting multiple options.

Icon buttons can be placed on a variety of backgrounds. Until the button is interacted with, its container isnt visible.

1:108.name: Icons/cancel_24px
1:108.description: cancel, exit, x, stop, close, circle

1:579.name: Style=outlined, State=focused, Text configurations=input-text, Leading icon=true, Trailing icon=True

1:2092.name: Configuration=Elevated, State=focused, Show Icon=False
1:2092.description:
Elevated buttons are are medium-emphasis buttons.
They are essentially filled tonal buttons with a shadow. Only use them when absolutely necessary, such as when the button requires visual separation from a patterned background.

1:2179.name: Configuration=Filled, State=focused, Show Icon=True
1:2179.description:
Filled buttons are high-emphasis buttons.
They have the most visual impact after the FAB, and should be used for important, final actions that complete a flow, like "Save", "Join now", or "Confirm".

1:1274.name: Style=filled, State=focused, Text configurations=input-text, Leading icon=true, Trailing icon=True

1:22.name: Icon button
1:22.description:
Icon buttons display actions in a compact layout. Icon buttons can represent opening actions such as opening an overflow menu or search, or represent binary actions that can be toggled on and off, such as favorite or bookmark.

Icon buttons can be grouped together or they can stand alone.

1:114.name: [m3:textfield] Text field
1:114.description:
Use a text field when someone needs to enter text into a UI, such as filling in contact or payment information.

 Additional options
Support text - you can toggle supporting text between hide and show.

1:2030.name: [m3:button] Button
1:2030.description: Buttons communicate actions that users can take. They are typically placed throughout your UI, in places like Dialogs, Modal windows, Forms, Cards and Toolbars
